Ok when JC was put into the game, most people rightly saw it as an enchanter only skill since they were the ones who got the spells to enchant the bars.

As an enchanter who makes jewelry, I have no objections to other classes making jewelery too. I mean i think it's unwise to do it unless you have enchanter friends but hey why should we enchanters complain? We can charge them to enchant bars which would make US more money. And according to these posts i guess not alot of people want to make more money :). But anyway who cares if they want to make jewelry. I read how one person compared this matter to shamans/druids/ and sow? You (almost) never see a druid or shaman totally refuse to spare a sow, or sell one. But also jewelry is permanent whereas the buff isn't. So when Verant saw this issue with the angry chanters they added, voila! Imbue Gem spells to the WIS classes. This somewhat balances the JCing issue and if chanters want to make other jewelry they now have to ask clerics/druids/shamans(?) to imbue the gems.

All in all it's childish to argue about enchanters being the only one to jewelcraft. I mean monks aren't the only one to tailor but hey they get the black pantherskin and such (BTW a big f.u.c.k you to Verant for giving BST's black pantherskin). Also about the twinks, hey if a person wants to twink their characters leave them alone, most of the jewelry you sell (well the velium and such) will most likely go to a twink eventually. SO stop bein hypocrits.

Yes i'm done
